The paper deals with the characterization of non-linear dimensionality reduction methods obtained by quantizing linear embeddings, which involves concepts from information theory (quantization) and machine learning (dimensionality reduction). Therefore, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of linear matrices with fast matrix-vector multiplication algorithms, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper derives upper bounds on the additive distortion induced by quantization, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM).
